---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import MainLayout from '@layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Divider from '@components/Divider.astro';
import labImage from '@assets/aerial.jpg';
import { paths } from '@data/paths';

const title = 'About us';
const description =
  'Clouder is on a mission to unlock the hidden value in real estate portfolios. We replace silos and fragmented operations with investment-grade data and turn it into measurable asset value.';
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section>
    <div class="pt-24 pb-8 lg:pt-48 lg:pb-16">
      <div class="container">
        <h1
          class="mb-4 max-w-prose font-serif text-4xl text-neutral-950 lg:mb-6 lg:text-6xl xl:text-7xl dark:text-neutral-50"
        >
          Unlocking hidden value<br class="hidden lg:block" /> in real estate portfolios
        </h1>
        <p class="max-w-prose leading-normal text-balance lg:text-lg">
          {description}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container px-0">
      <Image
        src={labImage}
        alt="People in hardware laboratory"
        class="aspect-video bg-neutral-500/10 object-cover object-top text-transparent"
        width={1280}
        layout="constrained"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="py-16 lg:py-32">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h2
              class="font-serif text-2xl text-neutral-950 lg:row-span-2 lg:text-3xl dark:text-neutral-50"
            >
              Turning building data<br class="hidden lg:block" /> into asset intelligence
            </h2>
            <p class="text-balance">
              We have been on the other side of this problem. As real estate investors, owners, and
              asset managers, we have sat through the transactions, reviewed the reports, and
              managed the portfolios. And we kept seeing the same thing: assets that should be
              consuming less energy and performing better. Every wasted euro is permanently off the
              asset value. So we decided to build what the industry was missing.
            </p>
            <p class="text-balance">
              We built a direct connection to building systems (not through cloud APIs, but at the
              source) that turns real building data into real operational value. Clouder doesn't
              just read data. It acts on it, in real time, and learns from the result. Every
              building gets smarter, consumes less energy, and produces fewer emissions. Every new
              asset benefits from what we have already learned across the portfolio. The system
              compounds.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h2
              class="font-serif text-2xl text-neutral-950 lg:row-span-2 lg:text-3xl dark:text-neutral-50"
            >
              Built by people who know real estate and technology
            </h2>
            <p class="text-balance">
              Clouder is built on an uncommon combination of expertise: decades of experience in
              large-scale commercial real estate development, transactions and institutional asset
              management, paired with deep knowledge in data architecture, real-time systems
              engineering and enterprise-scale technology infrastructure. That breadth of competence
              across both disciplines is what makes it possible to build something the industry has
              not seen before.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Divider />
  <section>
    <div class="py-16 lg:py-32">
      <div class="container-narrow space-y-4 text-center lg:space-y-6">
        <h2
          class="font-serif text-3xl text-neutral-950 lg:row-span-2 lg:text-5xl dark:text-neutral-50"
        >
          The gap is measurable.<br /><span class="opacity-50">So is closing it.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-balance">
          Clouder works with commercial real estate funds, asset managers, and large-scale investors
          who manage portfolios where operational inefficiency has real, measurable consequences. If
          you suspect the gap between your portfolio's current value and its potential is larger
          than it should be, we should talk.
        </p>
        <div>
          <a
            href={paths.contact.href}
            class="mt-1 inline-flex h-10 cursor-pointer items-center justify-center rounded bg-neutral-950 px-4 text-center text-sm text-nowrap text-neutral-50 transition select-none hover:bg-neutral-700 active:bg-neutral-700 dark:bg-neutral-50 dark:text-neutral-950 dark:hover:bg-neutral-300 dark:active:bg-neutral-300"
          >
            Get in touch
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
